&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/terms/neurotic-platformal-intellectual/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/terms/neurotic-platformal-intellectual/> ;
  schema:name "Neurotic platformal intellectual" ;
  schema:description "The structural subject-position produced when platforms industrialize the confessional incitement-to-discourse, turning every user into a performer of expertise whose intellectual labor is governed by anxiety, feeling rules, and platform-native logics of visibility. The position is *platformal* rather than *platformed*: the platform is not a tool the intellectual uses but the structural condition that produces the intellectual's mode of intellectuality. They think in threads, evaluate ideas by engagement, produce analysis in platform-native formats. The condition becomes sharpest under crisis, when the intellectual is incited to perform continued expertise on ideas about which they are themselves naive — and the platform's feeling rules format partial understanding as complete understanding." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-03" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-03" ;
  emsenn:Contrastswith "traditional-intellectual" , "slow-scholar" , "monastic-reader" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/terms/neurotic-platformal-intellectual/> ;
